    {
        "id": "ex07-comment",
        "type": "comment",
        "z": "ex07-tab",
        "name": "Setup required: point the node at a real ONNX model",
        "info": "This example uses a placeholder model path (/data/models/anomaly-model.onnx) — open the ml-inference node and change 'Model Path' to an .onnx (or TensorFlow.js model.json) file that exists on your Node-RED host before deploying. The function node builds a numeric feature vector [temperature, vibration, pressure, rpm] which the node converts to a tensor and feeds to the model; the prediction is attached to msg.prediction. Adjust 'Input Shape' if your model expects a fixed shape, e.g. [1,4].",
